	<LINE>M'Dowall, Esq.; vice-president, John Wither, Esq.;</LINE>
	<LINE>treasurer, D. A. Finlay, Esq. ; vice-treasurer, John</LINE>
	<LINE>Carson, Esq. ; directors, Messrs. D. Aitken, Samuel</LINE>
	<LINE>Milroy, M. C. Thomson, M. Fairley, R. M'Adam, and</LINE>
	<LINE>John Campbell ; surgeon. Dr. M'Gill ; secretar'y, Jas.</LINE>
	<LINE>M' William, writer, 163 West George Street.</LINE>
	<LINE>The society was instituted in 1791 for the purpose</LINE>
	<LINE>of providing a fund out of which certain allowances</LINE>
	<LINE>might be made to the ordinary members of the society</LINE>
	<LINE>during sickness, infirmity, and superannuation.</LINE>
	<LINE>The entry money for ordinary members is 10s. 6d.,</LINE>
	<LINE>besides quarter accounts in proportion to age. Hono-</LINE>
	<LINE>rary members are admitted on payment of £1 Is.</LINE>
	<LINE>and upwards to the benevolent fund.</LINE>
	<LINE>CITY OF GLASGOW NATIVE BENEVOLENT</LINE>
